The Herald Herald Reporter President Mnangagwa has arrived in Rwandan capital Kigali for that country’s Liberation Day Celebrations slated for tomorrow. He was received at the Kagame International Airport by the Rwanda Foreign Affairs Minister Dr Richard Sezibera. The President is accompanied by Minister of Foreign Affairs and International Trade Dr Sibusiso Moyo and senior Government officials. Tomorrow’s commemorations, which reflect on the end of the 1994 genocide in which extremist Hutus rose up against and massacred more than a million the minority Tutsis, is expected to be attended by seven African Heads of State and Government. More details to follow… 